{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The Apple File System (APFS) is a modern file system, optimized for responsiveness on Flash\/SSD storage, and designed for extensibility, security, and data integrity. APFS is now the default filesystem on iOS, tvOS, and watchOS. Learn about what’s new for APFS on the Mac and how to take advantage of its new features in your apps.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/715\/","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-715-Whats-New-in-Apple-File-System"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-715-whats-new-in-apple-file-system"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"What’s New in Apple File System","role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC17","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Co